<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-854-904  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 854 904.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Sept 18 1989 v10 n37 p4(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Virus outbreak rumored. (computer virus)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Thyfault, Mary E.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Friday, Oct 13, 1989 is slated as the day that two seriouscomputer viruses will be activated on microcomputers runningMSDOS.andP;  But experts believe that the media interest surroundingthe Columbus Day or Datacrime virus is just hype.andP;  There is moreconcern about the Jerusalem Virus, an older virus that is expectedto be much more common than the Datacrime virus.andP;  As new virusesare developed and released, the old viruses are spreadingexponentially.andP;  Observers do not recommend any special software orprocedure to prevent the outbreak of the viruses, although they docaution users to practice standard security measures, such asperforming daily back-ups of files, not sharing unauthorizedprograms, and using caution when downloading programs frombulletin boards.andP;  There is a free program available from CVIA thatcan identify all known viruses.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer VirusesMS-DOSComputer CrimesPublic Relations.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>